./docs/generated/image.md:187:`Dali::ConnectionTracker::ConnectionTracker` constructs the tracking base. Derive your image controller from `Dali::ConnectionTracker`, then connect signals from their owning view or trait APIs, such as `Dali::Ui::AnimatedImageView::ResourceReadySignal()`, `Dali::Ui::AnimatedImageView::AnimationFinishedSignal()`, or `Dali::Ui::InteractiveTrait::ClickedSignal()`.
./docs/generated/animated-image-view.md:42:`Dali::Ui::AnimatedImageView` can use a single animated image URL through `SetResourceUrl`, or a sequence of still images through `SetResourceUrls`. A URL sequence is useful when an animation is delivered as numbered image frames.
