./docs/generated/animated-image-view.md:67:    .SetResourceUrls(frames)
./docs/generated/animated-image-view.md:75:Setting `SetResourceUrl` clears any URL sequence, and setting `SetResourceUrls` clears the single URL. Use `GetResourceUrl` when the view is configured with a single URL, and `GetResourceUrls` when it is configured with a frame sequence.
./docs/generated/animated-image-view.md:191:    .SetResourceUrl("images/avatar.gif")
./docs/generated/animated-image-view.md:219:Use `ResourceReadySignal` to react when the image resource has finished loading and is ready to display. Use `AnimationFinishedSignal` to react when playback has completed its configured loop count. Both signals use a `Dali::Ui::View` callback parameter.
